Package org.beancp

Object to object mapping library for Java 8+.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Action
    No argument action interface.
    Map<S,D>
    Map configuration.
    Mapper
    Object to object mapper.
    MappingConvention
    Mapping convention.
    MappingsInfo
    Returns information of configured mappings.
    MapSetup<S,D>
    Interface for lambda expression used to configure map.
    TriConsumer<T1,T2,T3>
    Represents an operation that accepts three input arguments and returns no result.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BindingOption<S,D,T>
    Binding options used in Map.bind(java.util.function.Supplier, java.util.function.Consumer, org.beancp.BindingOption...) and Map.bindConstant(java.lang.Object, java.util.function.Consumer, org.beancp.BindingOption...).
    MapperBuilder
    Builds mapper implementation.
    Util  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MapperConfigurationException
    Indicates error in mappings configuration.
    MappingException
    Indicates error during mapping.
    NullParameterException
    Indicates null value for method parameter which do not allow nulls.

Package org.beancp Description

Object to object mapping library for Java 8+. For more information checkout project home page.
